description:
&lt;p&gt;InHealth sees more than 3 million patients each year and our pain management service is one of the most important solutions we provide. We help, support and teach patients to manage pain by delivering evidence-based cognitive behavioural therapy approaches as a multidisciplinary team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a &lt;strong&gt;Clinical Psychologist &lt;/strong&gt;to join our pain management team in&lt;strong&gt; Durham and Darlington&lt;/strong&gt;. This is a full-time role working &lt;strong&gt;37.5 hours per week, Monday to Friday.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What are the key responsibilities of the Psychologist’s role? &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Delivering relevant, effective and sensitive pain management to individuals and groups&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assessing, planning and reviewing patients’ pain management treatment appropriately, ensuring that specialist support is focused on the patient’s individual needs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Devising and reviewing plans of care aimed at helping patients to achieve their goals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Promoting patient education and understanding of pain, rehabilitation and self-management strategies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evaluation the outcome of care with the multi-disciplinary team, assessing the distress and emotional impact of pain&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What skills and experience will you need to apply?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;BSc in Psychology with a good understanding of cognitive behavioural therapy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Member of an appropriate professional body and to hold a valid registration (HCPC)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding of the bio-psychosocial nature of chronic pain experience and management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven knowledge of the requirements of a Psychologist’s role in the care of patients, their visitors and carers, and to colleagues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A high level of professionalism and technical standard of work, complying with relevant Codes of Practice&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work in a multidisciplinary team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What’s in it for you?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We can offer a highly competitive salary and aninnovative approach to personal and professional development, helping you to be the best version of you and giving you a real career pathway. &lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;InHealth is an equal opportunities employer and welcomes applications from all areas of the community.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
